description:
The purpose of the role is initially to support and further develop the Bank's Model Risk Management framework related to market data and market risk management.
Key objectives:
• Support quantitative methodology related project work on the market data replacement system (FMDM) project;
• Support data and static assessment and cleanup;
• Development and implement analytics to support zero curve stripping across the full range of curves (IR and FX) for the full time series history in a prototype and or production framework;
• Development and implement analytics to support hazard rate curve stripping across the full range of spread curves for the full time series history in a prototype and or production framework;
• Development of the tools, including visualization, required to support the analytics development and support analysis and risk management review of the resulting data;
• Develop methodology documentation to support model validation review whilst adhering to regulatory requirements and internal development standards;
• Provide detailed pre-emptive justification and ongoing review of the modelling choices and assumptions in support of model risk management;
• Communication and interaction with the different stakeholders and oversight bodies: Project Team, Global Markets, Risk Managers and Model Validation.

The role is a pivotal part of the RMA Team and an essential part of the Risk Department for ICBCS. This team has the primary responsibility for the analytics (methodology and models) used in the Risk Department.

